@startuml Parser_All_Formats_Comparison
!theme plain
title ETL Parser - All File Formats Processing Comparison

== COMMON PIPELINE START ==

start
:File Input;
note right
  .xml, .xlsx, .xls
  .csv, .txt
  (.gz, .zip, .tar.gz)
end note

:Decompress Check;

== FORMAT-SPECIFIC PROCESSING ==

split
  :XML Format;
  :SAX Parser;
  note right
    Event-based
    30+ Vendor Engines
    XML Validation
  end note
  :SAX Events → HashMap;
split again
  :XLSX Format;
  :Apache POI XSSFWorkbook;
  note right
    Modern Excel
    Sheet → Row → Cell
  end note
  :Workbook → HashMap;
split again
  :XLS Format;
  :Apache POI HSSFWorkbook;
  note right
    Legacy Excel
    Sheet → Row → Cell
  end note
  :Workbook → HashMap;
split again
  :CSV Format;
  :opencsv CSVReader;
  note right
    Delimiter parsing
    Line-by-line
  end note
  :CSV Lines → HashMap;
split again
  :TXT Format;
  :BufferedReader;
  note right
    Custom format
    Regex/Pattern
    Custom parsing
  end note
  :Text Lines → HashMap;
end split

== COMMON PIPELINE CONVERGENCE ==

:ParseMapper.mapping();
note right
  Format-agnostic mapping
  Data transformation
  Column value extraction
end note

:Build HashMap<String, String>;
note right
  Unified data structure
  All formats converge here
  objectKey → value pairs
end note

:ThreadPool Processing;
note right
  Parallel thread handling
  onParseThreadCount
  Batch processing
end note

:prepareRecord();
note right
  Delimiter-separated string
  resultFileDelimiter
  Standardized format
end note

:syncWriteIntoFile();
note right
  CSV Output
  {tableName}-{objectKey}.csv
  Append mode
end note

:CSV Intermediate File;
note right
  All formats → CSV
  Standard interchange format
  Ready for database load
end note

:LoaderFactory Selection;
note right
  Determine database type:
  - ORACLE
  - MSSQL
  - POSTGRESQL
  Based on loaderTarget
end note

:Bulk Database Insert;
note right
  Oracle: SQLLDR
  MSSQL: Native BCP
  PostgreSQL: COPY command
  Batch loading
end note

:Database Table Updated ✓;

stop

@enduml